# Smartlease Project Context

## What This Project Is
Smartlease is an AI-powered Ontario real estate document 
platform built with FastAPI (Python) + MCP server.
It fills official government and OREA forms using an 
AI agent powered by the Anthropic API.

## Tech Stack
- Backend: FastAPI + Python 3.12
- AI: Anthropic API (claude-sonnet-4-6)
- MCP: mcp[cli] package for MCP server
- Frontend: Single HTML file (public/index.html)
- Virtual environment: venv (activate with source venv/bin/activate)
- Deploy target: Railway.app

## File Structure
smartlease/
├── .env                  ← ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
├── .cursorrules          ← this file
├── requirements.txt      ← pip freeze output
├── main.py               ← FastAPI app, /api/chat endpoint,
│                            Anthropic agent with tools
├── mcp_server.py         ← MCP server exposing form tools
├── forms/
│   ├── lease.py          ← fill_lease(data) → HTML string
│   │                        Ontario Standard Lease Form 2229E
│   └── purchase.py       ← fill_purchase(data) → HTML string
│                            OREA Agreement of Purchase and Sale
│                            Form 100
└── public/
    └── index.html        ← Split panel UI: left=chat, 
                             right=document preview

## Key Functions
fill_lease(data: dict) -> str
  in forms/lease.py
  Takes landlord, tenant, property, rent, deposit data
  Returns complete HTML of filled Form 2229E

fill_purchase(data: dict) -> str  
  in forms/purchase.py
  Takes buyer, seller, property, price, brokerage data
  Returns complete HTML of filled Form 100

## API Endpoints (main.py)
POST /api/chat
  - Receives: {messages: [...], conversation_id: str}
  - Calls Anthropic API with tools
  - If tool called: executes fill_lease or fill_purchase
  - Returns: {message: str, filled_document: str | null}

GET /health
  - Returns: {status: "ok"}

## MCP Tools (mcp_server.py)
Tool 1: fill_lease_agreement
  - Fills Ontario Standard Lease (Form 2229E)
  - Input: all lease fields as defined in forms/lease.py

Tool 2: fill_purchase_and_sale
  - Fills OREA Form 100
  - Input: all purchase fields as defined in forms/purchase.py

## Agent System Prompt (in main.py)
The agent knows:
- Which form to use for which scenario
- All required fields for each form
- To ask questions one at a time conversationally
- To confirm before filling
- To call the appropriate tool when ready

## Color Scheme (index.html)
Primary navy: #1B3A5C
Accent green: #2E7D5E
Background: #F7F8FA
Surface: #FFFFFF
Border: #DDE1E8

## Important Rules
- Always use python3.12 and the venv
- Never hardcode the API key — always use .env
- Forms return HTML strings, never PDF directly
- Print to PDF is done via window.print() in browser
- MCP server runs separately from main FastAPI server
- Keep all form boilerplate text verbatim — never summarize